name: Please Read!!  Rotor control for the IDIOM Rotor-EZ board,
info:
This Flow is a modified PSTRotatorAZ Flow

This flow requiares Ham Supply's IDIOM Rotator-EZ  

with the RS-232 port installed and a FTDI serial port plugged into 

the Node-Red PC and configured.

Thank you to Tormod, LA9VKA for his clickable azimuth 

map integration and Dave wo2x exppertise for helping me with the 

changes required.

name: Draw Beam Actual
point to angle
Draw Beam Target
PST RotatorAZ map control
info:
Change udp target to IP address of computer running PST Rotator(AZ)

LA9VKA

name: Build Rotator String

func: rbe

name: Send Rotator
func: return msg;

name: Receive Rotator
func: return msg;

msg.payload=msg.payload.slice(0,3);
return msg;

name: Set Up Serial Connection
info:
Set this for YOUR FTDI Serial ports serial number 
in the /dev/serial directory.

Maake sure on the COM ports Setting it is 
set for 4800 Baud 8,N,1 and down on the 
line that says
"Split input ( on the charcter )" ONLY has 
a Semicolen in the box ( ; )

Set Default response timeout to 500ms

func: rbe
rbe

name: To String
func:
msg.payload = msg.payload.toString('utf8');
return msg;

msg.payload = "<CMD><UPDATE><CONTROL>TXTENTRYCALL</CONTROL><VALUE>" + msg.payload + "</VALUE></CMD><CMD><ACTION><VALUE>CALLTAB</VALUE></CMD>\r\n"

return msg;

msg.payload = msg.payload.substr(8,3);
return msg;
